				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p>Using the Box Plot Calculator is straightforward and quick:</p>=
								</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-13a7c63f elementor-wi=
dget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"13a7c63f" data-element_type=
=3D"widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p><strong data-start=3D"830" data-end=3D"850">1. Enter Your Data:=
</strong> Input your data points into the calculator=E2=80=99s text field. =
You can paste a list of numbers separated by commas, spaces, or new lines =
=E2=80=93 the tool is flexible in how it accepts data=E2=80=8B (For example=
, you might enter: <code data-start=3D"1104" data-end=3D"1133">5, 7, 7, 10,=
 12, 13, 13, 16</code>.) <em data-start=3D"1136" data-end=3D"1143">Note:</e=
m> You should have at least <strong data-start=3D"1169" data-end=3D"1186">f=
our data points</strong> to create a meaningful box plot, as fewer than fou=
r values don=E2=80=99t allow for a proper calculation of quartiles. You can=
 also copy and paste a column of numbers from a spreadsheet directly into t=
he input field.</p>								</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-128f11ba elementor-wi=
dget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"128f11ba" data-element_type=
=3D"widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p><strong data-start=3D"1490" data-end=3D"1511">2. Submit/Calcula=
te:</strong> Once your data is entered, click the <strong data-start=3D"154=
9" data-end=3D"1564">=E2=80=9CCalculate=E2=80=9D</strong> or <strong data-s=
tart=3D"1568" data-end=3D"1580">=E2=80=9CSubmit=E2=80=9D</strong> button. T=
he calculator will sort the data and compute the necessary statistics in th=
e background. It calculates the five key values (min, Q1, median, Q3, max) =
that will be used to draw the box plot.</p>								</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-bcf2d96 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"bcf2d96" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p><strong data-start=3D"1828" data-end=3D"1845">3. View Results:<=
/strong> The calculator displays the <strong data-start=3D"1878" data-end=
=3D"1901">five-number summary</strong> and <strong data-start=3D"1906" data=
-end=3D"1913">IQR</strong> for your dataset, and it generates the <strong d=
ata-start=3D"1953" data-end=3D"1965">box plot</strong> for you. The numeric=
al summary is typically shown alongside or below the chart for clarity. If =
there are any outliers, the tool will highlight or list them separately. Yo=
u=E2=80=99ll see the box-and-whisker diagram on the screen, illustrating th=
e distribution of your data.</p>								</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-5a71d3e elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-image" data-id=3D"5a71d3e" data-element_type=3D"widget=
" data-widget_type=3D"image.default">
